    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "So it turns out the performance degradation here is because tuweni-crypto's  `Hash` now has support for libSodium.  In theory, using libSodium will give us native hashing which should significantly improve performance. However, tuweni is checking if Sodium is available every single time it performs a hash operation.  For Teku that's a complete disaster.\n\nAnd when sodium is installed, we appear to immediately get an `OutOfMemoryError` when sodium tries to allocate memory.  Sadly there's no good way to disable libsodium checks in Tuweni at the moment.  Have raised a PR to be able to disable it: https://github.com/apache/incubator-tuweni/pull/347",
